The paper deals with the security of cyber-physical systems, which is a topic in the subfield of computer security (cs.CR). The proposed approach uses game theory to model the interactions between an attacker and a defender, which falls under the subfield of game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques to solve the game, which is a topic in the subfield of control systems (cs.SY). The approach also involves modeling the bounded rationality of the attacker and defender, which is a topic in the subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and cognitive science (cs.CY).
